    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fruits of several species in the genus Mangifera, but most often referring to the species Mangifera indica, native to India and Burma (Myanmar); it is a sweet orange-fleshed drupe which is much eaten as dessert, especially in the tropics, and is used in its unripe state to make chutney and jam.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
